WEBVTT

00:02.333 --> 00:05.176
[ Marvin Gaye's
"What's Going On" plays ]

00:05.176 --> 00:06.387
Dre: Upsets...

00:06.387 --> 00:08.469
[ Horn blares ]
 ♪ Mother, mother ♪

00:08.469 --> 00:12.133
...they're as American
 as apple pie...and obesity.

00:12.133 --> 00:14.265
♪ There's too many of you
crying ♪
  Yep, America has a love affair

00:14.265 --> 00:15.726
with upsets.

00:15.726 --> 00:18.059
♪ Brother, brother, brother ♪

00:18.059 --> 00:20.601
As a matter of fact, that's
 how the country got started.

00:20.601 --> 00:24.565
♪ There's far
too many of you dying ♪
  Those scrappy kids from
 the East Coast beat an empire.

00:24.565 --> 00:26.907
Here's the thing
 with an upset, though --

00:26.907 --> 00:29.610
someone wins and someone loses.

00:29.610 --> 00:32.703
And when that happens,
 the losing side always tries

00:32.703 --> 00:35.206
to look for where things
 went wrong.

00:35.206 --> 00:36.997
Yep.
 At the end of the day,

00:36.997 --> 00:40.871
no one wants to be on
 the losing side of an upset.

00:40.871 --> 00:43.584
But what happens when
 the winners and the losers

00:43.584 --> 00:44.965
are supposed to be
 on the same team?

00:44.965 --> 00:46.427
♪ What's going on? ♪

00:46.427 --> 00:47.668
Reporter: And there is it.
 Rainbow: Oh!

00:47.668 --> 00:49.590
We're officially calling it
 a win for Donald Trump.

00:49.590 --> 00:51.051
♪ What's going on ♪
 Dre: I'm really asking.

00:51.051 --> 00:52.843
♪ I'll tell you
what's going on ♪
  Seriously, what happens?

00:52.843 --> 00:54.305
No, no, no, no.

00:59.560 --> 01:02.643
It had been over two months
 since the election,

01:02.643 --> 01:06.026
but everyone was acting like
 it had only been two minutes.

01:06.026 --> 01:08.239
Bow, what's going on, dude?
Seriously?

01:08.239 --> 01:09.990
What?
 Everything you're wearing

01:09.990 --> 01:11.532
is from an NPR commercial.

01:11.532 --> 01:13.033
No, it's from
a Barney's sale.

01:13.033 --> 01:14.655
Really?
 Yeah.

01:14.655 --> 01:16.457
These UNICEF flip-flops
are from a Barney's sale?

01:16.457 --> 01:18.539
And this Covenant House
sweatshirt

01:18.539 --> 01:20.831
and Habitat for Humanity
sweatpants,

01:20.831 --> 01:23.043
Black Lives Matter button --
Barney's.

01:23.043 --> 01:24.545
Uh-huh.

01:24.545 --> 01:26.707
And why aren't you guys
dressed for school?

01:26.707 --> 01:28.209
We don't
have school today.

01:28.209 --> 01:29.880
They gave us
a day of reflection.

01:29.880 --> 01:31.672
A day of what?
 Reflection.

01:31.672 --> 01:32.713
It's a lot
to think about.

01:32.713 --> 01:34.425
Much needed,
if you ask me.

01:34.425 --> 01:37.678
My first 90 days as student-body
president have been rough.

01:37.678 --> 01:41.182
Valley Glen Prep is
a pressure cooker about to blow.

01:41.182 --> 01:43.103
And he tried to tell me
I stole his phone.
 Gomez: Joey.

01:43.103 --> 01:44.725
Joey.
 "No, I didn't
steal your phone.

01:44.725 --> 01:47.228
I stole your computer."
 Joseph Peterson,

01:47.228 --> 01:49.190
will you please
get back in your seat?

01:49.190 --> 01:51.071
I don't have to listen to you,
Ms. Gomez.

01:51.071 --> 01:52.653
They're about to ship you
back to your country.

01:52.653 --> 01:54.695
[ Students gasping ]
 Ship her back.

01:54.695 --> 01:57.198
[ All chanting "Ship her back" ]

01:57.198 --> 02:00.911
To be fair, Ms. Gomez is from
Spain, her visa is expiring,

02:00.911 --> 02:03.414
and she is looking forward
to seeing her abuela.

02:03.414 --> 02:06.167
But I'm pretty sure those kids
did not know that at that time.

02:06.167 --> 02:07.748
They did not.

02:07.748 --> 02:10.841
So, yeah, we got the day off
to prep for the Healing Rally.

02:10.841 --> 02:13.133
They asked me to read MLK's
"I Have a Dream" speech at it,

02:13.133 --> 02:14.675
so I'm trying to memorize it.

02:14.675 --> 02:16.637
Oh, that's fantastic!

02:16.637 --> 02:19.099
Healing Rally?

02:19.099 --> 02:20.931
Day of reflection?

02:20.931 --> 02:22.223
Are they gonna prorate
your tuition?

02:22.223 --> 02:25.025
Dre.
 Bow, that school is not cheap.

02:25.025 --> 02:28.319
I know.
 Four kids times two days.

02:28.319 --> 02:30.861
That's a pair of Jordan 3s
and a hoodie.

02:30.861 --> 02:32.152
Oh, my God.
 What?

02:32.152 --> 02:34.535
I don't need comforting?

02:34.535 --> 02:36.577
[ Sighs ]

02:36.577 --> 02:39.700
Ignore him. I am very proud
of you, sweetheart.

02:39.700 --> 02:43.414
And why don't you take
this Trevor Project scarf.

02:43.414 --> 02:46.457
Wear it around your throat
while you're practicing, huh?

02:46.457 --> 02:48.379
What are you doing for
the Healing Rally, Zoey?

02:48.379 --> 02:50.751
I'm making lemonade.
Looking up recipes now.

02:50.751 --> 02:54.965
Oh, I get it.

02:54.965 --> 02:58.389
The country gives you lemons,
and you make lemonade, right?

02:58.389 --> 02:59.300
Nope.

02:59.300 --> 03:02.433
Oh, I see.

03:02.433 --> 03:06.607
You're doing it more as
a symbolic thing, like Beyoncé.

03:06.607 --> 03:09.069
How she uses lemonade
as a symbol for women

03:09.069 --> 03:10.861
and their self-knowledge
and healing.

03:10.861 --> 03:12.022
Yeah, that's good.

03:12.022 --> 03:13.524
No, I mean it as

03:13.524 --> 03:15.696
a non-carbonated
refreshment thing.

03:15.696 --> 03:18.409
My friends are not really
soda people.

03:18.409 --> 03:19.870
Okay.

03:19.870 --> 03:21.322
Yeah, that's good, too.

03:21.322 --> 03:24.325
I mean, it's not scarf good,
but...do better.

03:24.325 --> 03:25.916
♪♪

03:25.916 --> 03:28.289
Your mother's unraveling.

03:28.289 --> 03:30.130
I'm probably gonna
have to get a lawyer

03:30.130 --> 03:31.882
to help me
take both of you.

03:31.882 --> 03:34.715
I've always wanted to testify
against one of my parents.

03:34.715 --> 03:36.967
I don't know why you guys don't
want to try my "stay positive"

03:36.967 --> 03:38.218
New Year's resolution.

03:38.218 --> 03:39.680
I'm telling you,
it helps.

03:39.680 --> 03:41.842
Like, I don't see
this glass as half empty,

03:41.842 --> 03:44.184
I see it as half full.

03:44.184 --> 03:45.346
But it's
completely empty.

03:45.346 --> 03:47.768
But I see it
as half full.

03:47.768 --> 03:49.019
It's also a bowl.

03:49.019 --> 03:50.481
♪♪

03:50.481 --> 03:54.565
In his own sweet-smiled,
 misunderstood way,

03:54.565 --> 03:57.658
Jack's confusion with metaphors
 seemed to echo

03:57.658 --> 04:01.031
the same polarizing emotions
 I saw everywhere I turned.

04:01.031 --> 04:03.073
[ Shouting indistinctly ]

04:03.073 --> 04:05.075
♪ I just need to clear my mind
now ♪

04:05.075 --> 04:07.328
The world had become
 a giant mixed vortex

04:07.328 --> 04:10.170
of anxiety and elation,
 and we seemed to be

04:10.170 --> 04:13.173
more openly divided
 than we'd been in a long time.

04:13.173 --> 04:15.255
♪ Now I know you not it ♪

04:15.255 --> 04:18.798
I wish I could say work
 was better, but it wasn't.

04:18.798 --> 04:21.221
♪ We could've been somebody ♪

04:21.221 --> 04:24.094
♪ Said you had
to tell somebody ♪

04:24.094 --> 04:27.348
♪ Let's take it back
to the first party ♪

04:27.348 --> 04:29.600
♪ When you tried
your first molly ♪

04:29.600 --> 04:32.102
♪♪

04:32.102 --> 04:34.895
Nope.
 Even the usually impenetrable,

04:34.895 --> 04:37.197
cartoonish walls
 of Stevens & Lido

04:37.197 --> 04:39.570
had been affected
 by the real uncertainties

04:39.570 --> 04:42.363
of what our world
 was going to become.

04:42.363 --> 04:44.204
[ Click ]
 -Come on, guys.
-Hey! Whoa.

04:44.204 --> 04:46.617
We've got till 5:00
to get this Boxable pitch ready.

04:46.617 --> 04:49.209
Whoa. Hold on. 5:00 today?
 Yeah.

04:49.209 --> 04:51.251
How the hell did we let this
creep up on us like that?

04:51.251 --> 04:52.333
Yeah, when did we get
that pitch?

04:52.333 --> 04:53.914
November 8th.

04:53.914 --> 04:55.676
Guys, listen up.
Listen up.

04:55.676 --> 04:58.919
Just got off the phone,
and we got the Boxable pitch.

04:58.919 --> 05:00.681
[ Cheers and applause ]

05:00.681 --> 05:02.513
This is huge.

05:02.513 --> 05:04.975
So huge, in fact,
that we brought back Lucy,

05:04.975 --> 05:08.599
completely unrelated to
the lawsuit we can't talk about.

05:08.599 --> 05:10.891
[ Neck cracks ]
 The point is, we have got to

05:10.891 --> 05:12.433
knock this pitch
out of the park.

05:12.433 --> 05:13.984
-I said "pitch."
-Did you?

05:13.984 --> 05:15.646
Didn't sound like it.

05:15.646 --> 05:18.399
Look, the good news is,
we have plenty of time,

05:18.399 --> 05:20.781
so I want you all to go home,
'cause tonight should be

05:20.781 --> 05:22.613
a pretty uneventful
election night.

05:22.613 --> 05:24.825
[ Cheers and applause ]

05:24.825 --> 05:26.367
We're gonna
make history tonight.

05:26.367 --> 05:28.248
Reporter:
 ...boisterous rally last night,

05:28.248 --> 05:29.870
Trump and his supporters,
 along...

05:29.870 --> 05:31.372
Everybody go home.

05:31.372 --> 05:33.123
There's no way we're
getting any work done today,

05:33.123 --> 05:35.215
so we'll reconvene tomorrow.

05:35.215 --> 05:37.838
I can't believe this.

05:37.838 --> 05:40.591
I just read that he may not
even live at the White House!

05:40.591 --> 05:43.724
What?! That is a donkey punch
to the back of the head.

05:43.724 --> 05:46.767
This day is a wash.
We'll start fresh tomorrow.

05:46.767 --> 05:48.178
Daphne:
This is ridiculous!

05:48.178 --> 05:50.521
I hear Sean Hannity's
already suggesting

05:50.521 --> 05:53.394
he basically do a reality show
inside the White House.

05:53.394 --> 05:57.237
Sweet mother of God,
that man is an evil genius.

05:57.237 --> 05:58.979
That's an outstanding idea.

05:58.979 --> 06:01.692
Look, there is no way we are
getting any work done today.

06:01.692 --> 06:03.824
No, no, no. We're gonna leave
the pitch for tomorrow.

06:03.824 --> 06:06.447
Now, come on, we got to get
some work done, all right?

06:06.447 --> 06:08.539
Now, these are the areas
that we need to focus on.

06:08.539 --> 06:10.701
Got to say, Leslie...
 [ Groans ]

06:10.701 --> 06:12.292
...I still can't believe
you didn't vote for him.

06:12.292 --> 06:14.294
You guys don't know me at all,
okay?

06:14.294 --> 06:17.257
Look, I am a ferocious
Republican,

06:17.257 --> 06:20.210
but Trump is just
not my kind of guy.

06:20.210 --> 06:23.343
Now, you give me a true
conservative like Mitt Romney --

06:23.343 --> 06:25.966
a beautiful, coiffed-haired
tax genius

06:25.966 --> 06:28.559
made in a president factory?
Mm-mmm!

06:28.559 --> 06:30.561
Also, your entire life
runs on the backs

06:30.561 --> 06:33.934
of an absurdly low-priced,
extremely diligent workforce

06:33.934 --> 06:35.646
Trump is looking
to deport.

06:35.646 --> 06:36.857
Also, there's that.
-Mm.

06:36.857 --> 06:37.858
Come on.
We got to move on.

06:37.858 --> 06:39.399
-Mm-hmm.
-Dre's right.

06:39.399 --> 06:41.522
I mean, we've tricked off the
last two months of work on this.

06:41.522 --> 06:43.153
-Yeah.
-Look, it's a new year,

06:43.153 --> 06:45.195
fresh start, clean slate.

06:45.195 --> 06:46.286
Curtis:
Uh, speaking of Slate --

06:46.286 --> 06:47.828
did y'all see
what they put up today?

06:47.828 --> 06:49.239
What?
 Trump is in a Twitter beef

06:49.239 --> 06:50.451
with Dikembe Mutombo.

06:50.451 --> 06:51.912
-Oh, hell.
-Guys!

06:51.912 --> 06:53.413
Guys!
-That's crazy.

06:53.413 --> 06:55.706
[ All talking ]

06:55.706 --> 06:57.628
Junior: I have a dream.

06:57.628 --> 07:00.300
[ As Martin Luther King Jr. ]
I have a dream.

07:00.300 --> 07:01.922
[ As Malcolm X ]
I have a dream.

07:01.922 --> 07:03.544
I have a dream that

07:03.544 --> 07:05.345
blah-de-blah-de-blip-blip
yadda-yadda.

07:05.345 --> 07:07.097
You know this
"I have a dream" stuff

07:07.097 --> 07:08.048
is not the whole speech,
right?

07:08.048 --> 07:09.049
It isn't?

07:09.049 --> 07:10.390
It most certainly is not.

07:10.390 --> 07:11.391
There's a whole lot
of that speech

07:11.391 --> 07:12.553
that they do not
want you to hear.

07:12.553 --> 07:15.015
And when I say "they,"
I do mean the white man,

07:15.015 --> 07:16.396
if I was not clear.

07:18.188 --> 07:19.520
I'm not feeling
this scarf, Junior.

07:23.774 --> 07:24.735
This was my life now.

07:24.735 --> 07:26.236
The idea of business as usual

07:26.236 --> 07:28.328
had become anything but usual.

07:28.328 --> 07:31.492
Nobody knew how we got here,
 but everybody had their ideas.

07:31.492 --> 07:33.664
Hey!
Keep it down, okay?

07:33.664 --> 07:35.996
'Cause we all know
whose fault this really is.

07:35.996 --> 07:38.919
I'm actually mad at myself
for not having started here.

07:38.919 --> 07:40.671
Okay.

07:40.671 --> 07:41.792
-Oh.
-What?!

07:41.792 --> 07:43.504
It was the blacks.

07:43.504 --> 07:45.636
You just can't give us
that capital "B," huh?

07:45.636 --> 07:47.888
Not today, Charles.
Not today.

07:47.888 --> 07:49.179
How is this our fault?

07:49.179 --> 07:50.591
If you all had turned out
for Hillary

07:50.591 --> 07:52.392
the way that you turned out
for Barack --

07:52.392 --> 07:55.355
Hold on. Are you comparing
Barack Obama to Hillary Clinton?

07:55.355 --> 07:57.267
That's exactly
what he's doing.

07:57.267 --> 07:58.729
T-That's just crazy.

07:58.729 --> 08:00.901
You're talking about the man
who had a left-hand jumper

08:00.901 --> 08:02.232
and smoked menthols.

08:02.232 --> 08:03.944
Coolest president
we ever had.

08:03.944 --> 08:05.235
I mean, no offense
to Hillary,

08:05.235 --> 08:07.608
but that's like comparing
Jay Z to k.d. lang.

08:07.608 --> 08:08.819
-Mm-hmm.
-I don't know about

08:08.819 --> 08:11.702
left-hand jumpers
or what a K.D. Lang is,

08:11.702 --> 08:13.373
and as much as I do love

08:13.373 --> 08:15.616
the cool legendary rush
of a menthol,

08:15.616 --> 08:16.997
all I cared about
was that he was black.

08:16.997 --> 08:18.579
-Yes.
-Yes.

08:18.579 --> 08:19.790
-There it is.
-He could've punched a baby

08:19.790 --> 08:20.791
in the face.

08:20.791 --> 08:21.962
-Broke his nose!
-What?!

08:21.962 --> 08:23.624
It wouldn't have mattered.
Look, come on.

08:23.624 --> 08:25.085
We talking about
the first black president ever.

08:25.085 --> 08:26.386
Okay.
 We had to come out.

08:26.386 --> 08:28.178
Don't even care that
he was a Republican.

08:28.178 --> 08:29.179
-Uh...
-Sorry?

08:29.179 --> 08:30.260
Oh. Um...

08:30.260 --> 08:32.633
He was -- He was
a Democrat, Charlie.

08:32.633 --> 08:34.183
Both times?

08:34.183 --> 08:37.017
-Oh.
-Yeah, both times.

08:37.017 --> 08:39.640
Hmm.
I'm gonna look that up.

08:39.640 --> 08:41.020
Wow.
 Maybe you should come up

08:41.020 --> 08:42.442
with an idea
for this pitch.
 Well...

08:42.442 --> 08:44.444
No, no, no.
I'm -- I'mma do this.

08:44.444 --> 08:46.486
Truth is, you got to rep
your people.

08:46.486 --> 08:49.860
That's why who we really
need to blame is white...

08:49.860 --> 08:51.321
Hold on one damn minute,
now!

08:51.321 --> 08:52.412
...women!

08:52.412 --> 08:53.493
Let's hear her out,
guys.

08:53.493 --> 08:55.155
I think she's got
something to say.

08:55.155 --> 08:57.327
When black folks had the chance
to put up one of ours,

08:57.327 --> 08:58.659
we did what we had to do.

08:58.659 --> 08:59.539
That's right.
-Come on now.

08:59.539 --> 09:00.871
Showed up
and showed out.

09:00.871 --> 09:02.793
And, Dre,
I got to be honest.

09:02.793 --> 09:04.504
-Yeah.
-I still don't see anything

09:04.504 --> 09:07.547
on here about that whole
Barack-Democrat thing.

09:07.547 --> 09:10.010
I'm gonna go to the library,
see what I can dig up.

09:10.010 --> 09:11.431
Okay.

09:11.431 --> 09:13.594
Also, I have to
return a DVD.

09:13.594 --> 09:15.886
I do not recommend
"Young Guns II."

09:15.886 --> 09:17.137
What?
 He might love it.

09:17.137 --> 09:18.558
It's a classic.

09:18.558 --> 09:19.890
Look.
Okay, seriously.

09:19.890 --> 09:21.481
That pant-suited white woman
could've been

09:21.481 --> 09:24.685
the first female president,
so can someone explain

09:24.685 --> 09:28.528
how 53% of white women voted for
the orange [bleep] grabber?

09:28.528 --> 09:31.071
I've always said
the American white woman

09:31.071 --> 09:33.243
is as fickle
as a Pinot Noir.

09:33.243 --> 09:35.405
Lucy, I mean,
as the resident white woman,

09:35.405 --> 09:38.869
if there was ever a cue for
you to talk, it would be now.

09:38.869 --> 09:41.201
Why didn't your sisters
turn out for Hillary?

09:43.083 --> 09:44.705
Why is she just
staring at me?

09:44.705 --> 09:46.837
Please, dear God,
just say something.

09:46.837 --> 09:48.128
[ Sighs ]
 Lucy?

09:48.128 --> 09:50.841
Well, first,
white women aren't sisters.

09:50.841 --> 09:52.132
We hate each other.

09:52.132 --> 09:53.674
-Okay.
-And second, if you must know...

09:55.716 --> 09:56.767
...I voted for Trump.

09:56.767 --> 09:58.769
[ Screaming ]
 Oh, my God!

09:58.769 --> 09:59.850
No, you didn't!

09:59.850 --> 10:01.431
Pinot Noir.

10:01.431 --> 10:03.523
Unh-unh.
She ain't worth it.

10:03.523 --> 10:06.687
And there will be neither rest
nor tranquility in America

10:06.687 --> 10:09.609
until the Negro is granted
his citizenship rights.

10:09.609 --> 10:11.281
The whirlwinds of revolt
will continue

10:11.281 --> 10:13.533
to shake the foundations
of our nation

10:13.533 --> 10:16.616
until the bright day
of justice emerges.

10:16.616 --> 10:18.368
Oh, my God.

10:18.368 --> 10:19.870
You were right.

10:19.870 --> 10:21.371
That's a battle cry.

10:21.371 --> 10:22.953
It's like something
from "Braveheart."

10:22.953 --> 10:25.245
Martin had a lot more Malcolm
in him than people thought.

10:25.245 --> 10:27.167
It's like
two different speeches.

10:27.167 --> 10:29.009
Why don't they teach us
  this part?

10:29.009 --> 10:30.671
'Cause it's their job
to pacify you,

10:30.671 --> 10:32.462
and when I say "they,"
I do mean the white man,

10:32.462 --> 10:33.343
if I wasn't clear.

10:33.343 --> 10:34.424
It's a scam!

10:34.424 --> 10:35.716
Sure,
they give us the hook,

10:35.716 --> 10:37.057
but they don't give us
the verse.

10:37.057 --> 10:38.558
You can find me
up in the club,

10:38.558 --> 10:40.640
but what else is
going down there?

10:40.640 --> 10:42.142
Oh, a whole lot, son.
A whole lot.

10:42.142 --> 10:43.183
Well, go ahead.
Have a sip.

10:43.183 --> 10:45.185
No, no, don't do that.
Don't do that.

10:45.185 --> 10:46.356
Besides, you're underage

10:46.356 --> 10:47.768
and you look like
you might have the gene.

10:47.768 --> 10:49.479
I can feel it sometimes.

10:49.479 --> 10:51.231
Look, I know you're
feeling duped right now.

10:51.231 --> 10:53.323
I've been there. But you
can't let it get you down.

10:53.323 --> 10:55.445
The day you realize that
there are things going on

10:55.445 --> 10:57.237
between the lines
is a special day.

10:57.237 --> 10:59.780
But how can I read
this one section

10:59.780 --> 11:01.702
knowing it's not
the complete message?

11:01.702 --> 11:03.784
It's just a choice you're gonna
have to make for yourself.

11:03.784 --> 11:05.045
Thank God I got alcohol
to help me

11:05.045 --> 11:06.456
with these
difficult decisions.

11:06.456 --> 11:07.587
You --
you're on your own.

11:07.587 --> 11:09.049
Can I have, like, a sip?

11:09.049 --> 11:11.381
Oh, I'm definitely gonna
have to keep my eye on you.

11:11.381 --> 11:13.964
Stevens:
Lucy, you sound stupid, okay?

11:13.964 --> 11:16.596
There's all this yappity-yap
about female empowerment,

11:16.596 --> 11:18.218
and still
you don't care enough

11:18.218 --> 11:19.299
to elect the first
female president?

11:19.299 --> 11:21.852
Of course I want
a female president.

11:21.852 --> 11:23.603
I just didn't want it
to be her.

11:23.603 --> 11:24.765
-Why?
-Why?

11:24.765 --> 11:26.476
You guys just said that
you would've voted for

11:26.476 --> 11:28.608
anyone who was black,
but what if instead of Obama,

11:28.608 --> 11:32.312
it was Clarence Thomas
or Herman Cain or Ben Carson?

11:32.312 --> 11:33.904
-Oh, God, no.
-Definitely not that fool.

11:33.904 --> 11:35.365
Dude is a weirdo.

11:35.365 --> 11:36.907
Yeah, exactly.
Well, in my mind,

11:36.907 --> 11:38.869
Hillary Clinton is
the Ben Carson of white women.

11:38.869 --> 11:40.240
-Oh.
-What?!

11:40.240 --> 11:41.912
-Outrageous.
-Is Ben Carson even black?

11:41.912 --> 11:43.493
But Trump's a misogynist.

11:43.493 --> 11:45.125
I mean,
t-t-the boob jokes,

11:45.125 --> 11:47.207
the Miss Universe comments,
the [bleep] grabbing?

11:47.207 --> 11:48.418
-Ah.
-Man, totally ruined Tic Tacs

11:48.418 --> 11:49.709
for me.

11:49.709 --> 11:51.962
Look, as stupid as those
comments were, and they were,

11:51.962 --> 11:53.754
at least I know
he says what's on his mind.

11:53.754 --> 11:55.756
Who knows what Hillary's
actually thinking?

11:55.756 --> 11:57.427
What was she even about?

11:57.427 --> 11:59.970
Oh, my God. Stop it!
What was she even about?

11:59.970 --> 12:01.842
She was the most
qualified candidate

12:01.842 --> 12:03.764
to ever run for president.

12:03.764 --> 12:06.106
Look, I'll admit, I don't think
Donald Trump is a great guy.

12:06.106 --> 12:08.438
No, he is the devil,
and I should know.

12:08.438 --> 12:09.559
-What?
-Hmm?

12:09.559 --> 12:11.401
But look, Hillary's
no angel, either.

12:11.401 --> 12:13.273
I'm not some crazy
right-wing nut, you guys.

12:13.273 --> 12:14.654
I voted for Obama twice.

12:14.654 --> 12:17.117
I even got my Republican parents
to vote for him.

12:17.117 --> 12:18.408
He felt different.

12:18.408 --> 12:20.410
I believed he was
gonna change stuff.

12:20.410 --> 12:22.282
He did!
 But it's eight years later,

12:22.282 --> 12:24.324
and my dad's still out of work,
my hometown's about to go under,

12:24.324 --> 12:26.036
and Hillary comes out saying

12:26.036 --> 12:28.748
she's basically gonna
keep everything the same.

12:28.748 --> 12:31.541
I'm sorry, but that doesn't work
for me or my family.

12:31.541 --> 12:33.373
Okay, I-I-I hear
what you're saying.

12:33.373 --> 12:35.215
But what about
all the other families

12:35.215 --> 12:36.676
that are gonna
be affected --

12:36.676 --> 12:39.299
Gay families, Muslim families,
immigrant families?

12:39.299 --> 12:40.881
And we're in here
fighting against

12:40.881 --> 12:42.642
the greatness of America again,
aren't we?

12:42.642 --> 12:44.474
Pumpkin, that is not
how I raised you.

12:44.474 --> 12:46.646
What?
I was allowed to hit the help.

12:46.646 --> 12:48.889
Uh, that was just exercise.
You were pudgy.

12:48.889 --> 12:50.480
I'm sorry, but just think about
it for a second.

12:50.480 --> 12:53.233
This country at its core
is just a company.

12:53.233 --> 12:54.855
I mean, I know we don't like
to think of it that way,

12:54.855 --> 12:57.157
but America is a corporation,
okay?

12:57.157 --> 13:00.280
It's the world's biggest
and most important corporation.

13:00.280 --> 13:03.613
So is it so crazy to think
that maybe a businessman,

13:03.613 --> 13:06.957
who runs big corporations,
might not be such a bad idea?

13:06.957 --> 13:08.538
He runs them
into the ground.

13:08.538 --> 13:10.500
-Exactly.
-That idiot goes bankrupt

13:10.500 --> 13:12.792
like Khloé Kardashian
changes black dudes.

13:12.792 --> 13:15.415
Well, guess what.
He won, okay?

13:15.415 --> 13:17.177
So can we please
give this man a chance?

13:17.177 --> 13:18.338
-To do what?
-Hell no!

13:18.338 --> 13:20.090
Chance to what?
 At least give him a chance.

13:20.090 --> 13:21.511
Dre: Guys!

13:21.511 --> 13:24.724
Guys, the pitch is today,
all right?

13:24.724 --> 13:26.186
Can we get back
to work?

13:26.186 --> 13:28.308
-Fine.
-Fine.

13:28.308 --> 13:30.640
As long as she knows
that a vote for Trump

13:30.640 --> 13:31.982
is a vote for racism.

13:31.982 --> 13:33.523
-Yep, very true.
-Oh, I'm racist?

13:33.523 --> 13:34.774
-Mm-hmm.
-I'm a racist?

13:34.774 --> 13:35.605
-Yep, pretty much.
-I'm a racist?

13:35.605 --> 13:36.816
Please, don't say it.

13:36.816 --> 13:37.938
I have black friends.

13:37.938 --> 13:39.819
-Oh!
-Oh, my God. She said it.

13:39.819 --> 13:41.611
It's racist to say that.
-They're real. They're real.

13:41.611 --> 13:42.612
-Lunch!
-I do!

13:42.612 --> 13:43.783
It's lunch.

13:43.783 --> 13:45.115
Rainbow:
So, for my donation,

13:45.115 --> 13:47.747
I get a water bottle
and a Frisbee.

13:47.747 --> 13:48.949
That is awesome.

13:48.949 --> 13:50.790
Go, Hillary!

13:50.790 --> 13:52.292
Yeah, I-I know.

13:52.292 --> 13:54.214
Thank you.
 [ Telephone beeps ]

13:54.214 --> 13:55.715
Still working
on your lemonade, huh?

13:55.715 --> 13:56.917
I am.

13:56.917 --> 13:58.168
Okay.

13:58.168 --> 13:59.759
Did you know
the yellower the lemon,

13:59.759 --> 14:01.221
the more tart the taste?

14:01.221 --> 14:03.924
Did you know that the Earth
has lost more

14:03.924 --> 14:06.386
than half of its wildlife
in the last 40 years?

14:06.386 --> 14:07.968
Whoa. That's a lot.

14:07.968 --> 14:10.180
That's a lot.
 Thank God for zoos.

14:10.180 --> 14:13.894
How about while
that's cooking,

14:13.894 --> 14:15.815
you and I
just take 15 minutes

14:15.815 --> 14:18.899
and hop on a Planned Parenthood
phone bank

14:18.899 --> 14:20.860
and make them some money?

14:20.860 --> 14:23.283
'Cause we're women, sweetie,
and people hate us.

14:23.283 --> 14:24.444
I can't, Mom.

14:24.444 --> 14:27.487
Got to keep stirring this
60 rotations a minute,

14:27.487 --> 14:28.578
or else it'll clot.

14:28.578 --> 14:30.700
You know
what else will clot?

14:30.700 --> 14:33.333
Untreated
rectovaginal fistulas.

14:33.333 --> 14:35.996
I've really got to focus
on this.

14:35.996 --> 14:38.838
-How is he getting Mexico...
-I want you to explain that.

14:38.838 --> 14:41.841
He's gonna start arresting women
for having abortions.

14:41.841 --> 14:44.134
He walked that back,
and maybe you wouldn't
have to worry about that

14:44.134 --> 14:46.466
if 650,000 e-mails
didn't disappear...

14:46.466 --> 14:48.388
[ All shouting ]

14:48.388 --> 14:51.011
We're talking about e-mails.
Not policy, e-mails.

14:51.011 --> 14:52.602
See what I did there?

14:52.602 --> 14:55.015
Look, all I know is that man
would never be my president.

14:55.015 --> 14:56.316
-Agreed.
-Agreed.

14:56.316 --> 14:57.517
What about
the electoral college?

14:57.517 --> 14:58.688
I mean, there is still time
to overturn that.

14:58.688 --> 14:59.729
No. No, no, no.

14:59.729 --> 15:01.481
[ Chuckles ]

15:01.481 --> 15:03.653
Wait, no, no, no. Hold on.
W-What's so funny, Dre?

15:03.653 --> 15:06.656
Yeah, you haven't had nothing to
say about any of this all day.

15:06.656 --> 15:09.829
Why do you not care about
what's happening to our country?

15:11.661 --> 15:12.872
What did you say to me?

15:12.872 --> 15:14.955
Hmm?

15:14.955 --> 15:17.998
You don't think
I care about this country?

15:17.998 --> 15:19.459
I love this country,

15:19.459 --> 15:22.382
even though at times,
it doesn't love me back.

15:22.382 --> 15:28.258
For my whole life,
my parents, my grandparents, me,

15:28.258 --> 15:32.812
for most black people, this
system has never worked for us.

15:32.812 --> 15:34.474
♪ Southern trees ♪

15:34.474 --> 15:36.936
But we still played ball,
tried to do our best

15:36.936 --> 15:39.479
to live by the rules
even though we knew

15:39.479 --> 15:41.231
they would never work out
in our favor.

15:41.231 --> 15:42.983
♪ Bear a strange fruit ♪

15:42.983 --> 15:46.486
Had to live in neighborhoods
that you wouldn't drive through,

15:46.486 --> 15:48.948
send our kids to schools
with books so beat up

15:48.948 --> 15:50.740
you couldn't read them,

15:50.740 --> 15:54.204
work jobs that you wouldn't even
consider in your nightmares.

15:54.204 --> 15:56.706
♪ And blood at the roots ♪

15:56.706 --> 16:00.380
Black people wake up every day
believing that our lives

16:00.380 --> 16:03.423
are gonna change, even though
everything around us

16:03.423 --> 16:04.924
says it's not.

16:04.924 --> 16:07.507
♪ ...swinging
in the southern breeze ♪

16:07.507 --> 16:09.929
Truth be told,
you ask most black people,

16:09.929 --> 16:12.552
and they tell you that no matter
who won this election,

16:12.552 --> 16:14.354
they didn't expect the hood
to get better.

16:14.354 --> 16:15.895
♪ Strange fruit ♪

16:15.895 --> 16:17.687
But they still voted,

16:17.687 --> 16:20.600
because that's what
you're supposed to do.

16:20.600 --> 16:23.483
You think I'm not sad
that Hillary didn't win?

16:23.483 --> 16:25.905
That I'm not terrified about
what Trump's about to do?

16:28.238 --> 16:30.950
I'm used to things
not going my way.

16:30.950 --> 16:33.573
I'm sorry that you're not
and it's blowing your mind,

16:33.573 --> 16:36.286
so excuse me
if I get a little offended

16:36.286 --> 16:38.498
because I didn't see
all of this outrage

16:38.498 --> 16:41.251
when everything was happening
to all of my people

16:41.251 --> 16:45.545
since we were stuffed on boats
in chains.

16:45.545 --> 16:47.757
I love this country

16:47.757 --> 16:50.590
as much, if not more,
than you do,

16:50.590 --> 16:52.512
and don't you ever
forget that.

16:52.512 --> 16:56.015
♪♪

17:03.143 --> 17:05.315
Okay! I found the perfect way
for you to get involved.

17:05.315 --> 17:07.817
Mannequin challenge.
Ha!

17:07.817 --> 17:09.529
Just have to stand still.

17:09.529 --> 17:11.111
You literally
don't have to do anything.

17:11.111 --> 17:12.612
And then you can post it.

17:12.612 --> 17:14.114
You know, to raise awareness
on whatever you want?

17:14.114 --> 17:15.865
I'm not doing that, Mom.
 Why not?

17:15.865 --> 17:17.577
Zoey,
what's wrong with you?

17:17.577 --> 17:19.618
You have to have a voice.

17:19.618 --> 17:21.461
You don't want me
to have a voice,

17:21.461 --> 17:23.123
you want me to have
  your voice.

17:23.123 --> 17:24.464
Yeah.
 You think I don't see

17:24.464 --> 17:26.756
what's going on around us?

17:26.756 --> 17:29.379
That's why I made this lemonade
for the Healing Rally.

17:29.379 --> 17:33.012
It's not Liberal lemonade.
It's not Conservative lemonade.

17:33.012 --> 17:36.596
It's just lemonade
that I made with love.

17:36.596 --> 17:39.849
That's what I want my
contribution to be -- love.

17:41.851 --> 17:44.144
I'm sorry that
I have been acting

17:44.144 --> 17:45.605
the way that
I've been acting.

17:45.605 --> 17:47.987
I'm just --
I'm really upset.

17:47.987 --> 17:49.819
And I'm scared.

17:49.819 --> 17:54.324
And I don't want to hate people,
but I kind of do.

17:54.324 --> 17:56.536
'Cause honestly,
I feel hated.

17:57.827 --> 17:59.699
I feel like I failed you.

17:59.699 --> 18:02.372
What are you
talking about?

18:02.372 --> 18:06.966
Because as a mom, it is
my job to deliver a world

18:06.966 --> 18:09.669
where the values that I raised
you to believe in mattered.

18:09.669 --> 18:11.841
And they didn't!
They didn't!

18:11.841 --> 18:14.174
I mean, half of our country
rejected them!

18:14.174 --> 18:17.387
Hey, Mom, our values
don't disappear

18:17.387 --> 18:20.720
just because our side
lost one election.

18:20.720 --> 18:23.433
And in the next one,

18:23.433 --> 18:25.355
me and my friends
will be voting.

18:25.355 --> 18:28.067
We're gonna pick up
right where you left off.

18:29.729 --> 18:31.821
I know you will.

18:31.821 --> 18:33.573
Thank God.

18:33.573 --> 18:35.575
[ Chuckles ]

18:35.575 --> 18:37.577
Mm.

18:37.577 --> 18:38.698
Not bad?

18:38.698 --> 18:39.999
I mean, seriously.

18:39.999 --> 18:42.121
Yeah.
 This is fantastic.

18:42.121 --> 18:44.083
I'm really good.
 [ Laughs ]

18:44.083 --> 18:45.124
This is crazy.

18:45.124 --> 18:46.876
Tell me what I'm gonna say.

18:46.876 --> 18:48.338
Ain't nobody's pawn.

18:48.338 --> 18:49.379
What's going on here,
boy?

18:49.379 --> 18:51.381
I've been such a fool!

18:51.381 --> 18:53.463
Nothing is what it seems!

18:53.463 --> 18:56.556
The constitution,
the JFK assassination,

18:56.556 --> 18:58.388
"The Star Spangled Banner."

18:58.388 --> 19:00.180
Have you heard verse four?

19:00.180 --> 19:02.182
It's about
killing slaves!

19:02.182 --> 19:04.564
Yeah, you won't hear them
singing that at the Super Bowl.

19:04.564 --> 19:07.026
I'm gonna give a speech,
but it's gonna be

19:07.026 --> 19:09.399
a different kind of speech
that shakes the world.

19:09.399 --> 19:11.030
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Sit down, now.

19:11.030 --> 19:13.193
This is not what I meant.

19:13.193 --> 19:15.485
When I asked you
to read MLK's speech,

19:15.485 --> 19:17.367
it's 'cause I wanted you
to learn the truth,

19:17.367 --> 19:19.279
to know exactly
what you were talking about,

19:19.279 --> 19:20.870
but I didn't want you
to change who you are.

19:20.870 --> 19:22.081
But I'm woke now.

19:22.081 --> 19:23.663
And that's
a beautiful thing,

19:23.663 --> 19:26.045
but you can't let that turn you
into another angry black man.

19:26.045 --> 19:27.547
That's what I am.

19:27.547 --> 19:29.339
Hell, so is your daddy,
especially when he's hungry.

19:29.339 --> 19:31.050
But not you, son.

19:31.050 --> 19:32.462
That beautiful,
bright way you have

19:32.462 --> 19:34.714
of looking at the world
is what makes you special.

19:34.714 --> 19:36.636
I never want to take that
from you.

19:36.636 --> 19:39.349
Now, look, there was
something I didn't tell you

19:39.349 --> 19:41.100
about the speech.

19:41.100 --> 19:43.473
When Dr. King was giving
the speech, he was fired up.

19:43.473 --> 19:46.105
Now, there was a famous singer
named Mahalia Jackson

19:46.105 --> 19:47.397
sitting right there
with Dr. King.

19:47.397 --> 19:48.608
She screamed at him,
she said,

19:48.608 --> 19:50.019
"Tell them about your dream,
Martin!

19:50.019 --> 19:51.941
Tell them about your dream!"

19:51.941 --> 19:53.613
You see what I'm saying?

19:53.613 --> 19:55.114
You know I don't.

19:55.114 --> 19:59.529
Mahalia had heard Dr. King speak
in church a few nights before.

19:59.529 --> 20:01.821
She heard the speech --
the part about the dream.

20:01.821 --> 20:03.202
She was moved.

20:03.202 --> 20:05.084
So when Martin heard her
screaming,

20:05.084 --> 20:06.786
he knew immediately
what she meant.

20:06.786 --> 20:09.379
The people needed to hear
that we should be fighting.

20:09.379 --> 20:11.461
But they also needed to hear

20:11.461 --> 20:15.004
what we should be
fighting for -- the dream.

20:15.004 --> 20:17.837
Martin knew that.
You need to know that.

20:17.837 --> 20:22.011
And you especially need to know
it with where we are now.

20:22.011 --> 20:24.684
I'm feeling this look on you,
too.

20:31.401 --> 20:34.774
Look, I'm sorry
for blowing up like that.

20:34.774 --> 20:37.697
This election
is driving me crazy, too,

20:37.697 --> 20:40.700
and I know how hard it is
to deal with the gut punch

20:40.700 --> 20:43.072
that we are all feeling
right now.

20:43.072 --> 20:44.914
It sucks.

20:44.914 --> 20:47.867
And all I'm trying to say
is that maybe instead

20:47.867 --> 20:51.581
of letting this destroy us,
we take the feeling

20:51.581 --> 20:55.675
you guys felt the day after
the election...

20:55.675 --> 20:58.928
and say that morning
we all woke up

20:58.928 --> 21:01.591
knowing what it felt like
to be black.

21:03.883 --> 21:06.095
It is a nightmare.

21:06.095 --> 21:08.348
I thought
I'd feel taller.

21:08.348 --> 21:11.811
Yeah, well, maybe we can
get past all that racial B.S.

21:11.811 --> 21:14.944
that's held us up for so long
and work with each other

21:14.944 --> 21:17.236
to make sure that whatever
happens next in this country,

21:17.236 --> 21:18.488
we do together.

21:18.488 --> 21:22.111
How do we work together
when the other half is nuts?

21:22.111 --> 21:23.993
O-Okay, okay.
 Mm-hmm.

21:23.993 --> 21:25.825
We have to stop that,
too.

21:25.825 --> 21:28.958
All right, do I understand
what anybody in their right mind

21:28.958 --> 21:30.410
could have seen in Trump?

21:30.410 --> 21:33.543
No!
But maybe that's why we lost.

21:33.543 --> 21:38.177
Over 50 million people
felt something.

21:38.177 --> 21:40.550
And I'm not saying
that they were right.

21:40.550 --> 21:44.474
But I don't think it --
it's possible that all, half,

21:44.474 --> 21:47.186
or even most of them
were nuts...

21:48.598 --> 21:49.479
...or racists...

21:50.890 --> 21:52.141
...or hated women.

21:52.141 --> 21:53.853
So then what
were they thinking?

21:53.853 --> 21:55.895
Daphne, I don't know.

21:55.895 --> 22:00.740
But I do feel it's time that we
stop calling each other names

22:00.740 --> 22:04.494
and we start trying to have
those conversations.

22:04.494 --> 22:07.367
If we don't, we'll
end up being in a country

22:07.367 --> 22:10.159
that's even more divided
for a long time.

22:12.121 --> 22:17.086
King: There will be neither rest
nor tranquility in America

22:17.086 --> 22:21.340
until the Negro is granted
his citizenship rights.

22:21.340 --> 22:23.593
The whirlwinds of revolt
will continue

22:23.593 --> 22:26.516
to shake the foundations
of our nation

22:26.516 --> 22:31.391
until the bright day
of justice emerges.

22:31.391 --> 22:37.817
I have a dream that one day
on the red hills of Georgia

22:37.817 --> 22:40.109
the sons of former slaves

22:40.109 --> 22:42.902
and the sons
of former slave owners

22:42.902 --> 22:45.364
will be able to...
 Dre: I've been lucky enough
 to raise

22:45.364 --> 22:47.697
four beautiful children
 in the world that showed them

22:47.697 --> 22:51.451
Jay Z and Beyoncé
 as king and queen,

22:51.451 --> 22:53.623
a black family
 in the White House,

22:53.623 --> 22:55.705
and a woman run and almost win

22:55.705 --> 22:58.167
the presidency
 of the United States.

22:58.167 --> 23:00.420
So if you ask me
 if I love America,

23:00.420 --> 23:03.803
the answer is yes,
 warts and all.

23:03.803 --> 23:06.345
Can it be better?
 I hope so.

23:06.345 --> 23:10.269
And I hope that we as a people
 have it in us to come together

23:10.269 --> 23:12.682
and make lemonade
 out of our lemons.

23:12.682 --> 23:15.435
...and sing in the words
of the old Negro spiritual,

23:15.435 --> 23:18.518
